) and to the fact that its expression profile follows the pattern of nepetalactone changes during the development of
N. rtanjensis leaves
(
). However, current results point out
IS 2
as the more responsive isoform in NL biosynthesis during the exposure of
N. rtanjensis
and
N. argolica ssp. argolica
leaves to dehydration conditions.

In vitro cultures of
Nepeta rtanjensis Diklić & Milojević
and
Nepeta argolica Bory & Chaub. ssp. argolica
(syn.
Nepeta sibthorpii Bentham
,
Nepeta argolica Bory & Chaub.
) ( Lamiaceae ) were established from seeds and grown under the conditions described in previous publications (
;
). Plant material for the experiment was obtained by micropropagation of one selected genotype, using single-node stem segments as explants, and subcultivation was performed every 4 weeks. Plants were grown in 250 ml Erlenmeyer flasks containing 100 ml of solid ½ MS culture medium (
), made with modifications as in
.

Gene expression was quantified by real-time PCR using QuantStudio™ 3 Real-Time PCR System (Life Technologies, 
USA
). Thermocycler conditions were as follows: 95 °C for 10 min; 40 cycles of 95 °C for 15 s; 60 °C for 30 s; 72 °C for 30 s; and final extension at 72 °C for 10 min. The reactions were performed using Maxima SYBR Green/ ROX Master Mix (2X) (Thermo Fisher Scientific, 
USA
), cDNA corresponding to 
50 ng
RNA and 0.3 μM primers, according to the manufacturer's recommendations. The expression levels of putative NL pathway genes and transcription factors were calculated according to the 2 
−ΔΔCt
method (

) using either 18S rRNK or GAPDH as a housekeeping gene, as mentioned above. The data represent means ± SE from three replicates.

Statistical analyses, comparing the data at 1, 3 and 6 DPT and their respective non-treated controls, were performed by unpaired Students’ t-test. Paired 
t
-test was used to compare the gene expression values between abraded leaves and detached trichomes. T-tests were performed in GraphPad Prism 5.03 software, and a difference of p ≤ 0.05 was considered significant. Pearson correlation between transcript copy numbers was used to estimate the co-regulation of gene expression, which was visualized by a heatmap. This was performed in the 
R
statistical language (
R

) using the packages stats (
R

) and gplots (

).
